\[
\begin{cases}
x + y = 17 \\
x - y = 1
\end{cases}
\]
and
\[
\begin{cases}
x + y = -17 \\
x - y = -1
\end{cases}
\]
Adding these pairs of equations gives us the solutions:
\begin{cases}
2x = 18 \implies x = 9 \\
2y = 16 \implies y = 8
\end{cases}
and
\begin{cases}
2x = -18 \implies x = -9 \\
2y = -16 \implies y = -8
\end{cases}
So the integer solutions are $(9, 8)$, $(9, -8)$, $(-9, 8)$, and $(-9, -8)$. Thus, there are 4 lattice points.
